$interpreted: Pang: Yao! Where are you!?
Yao: Quiet down, will you?
Pang: Yao, why are you hiding here?
Yao: You idiot, didn't I tell you to quiet down?
Yao: Quit being so obvious and hide!
Pang: Who are those people?
Yao: Thieves.
Pang: Truly? Them?
Yao: You'd doubt my judgment?
Pang: No, it's not that, but... shouldn't we notify the proper authorities?
Yao: The "authorities" only care about their own interests, not trifles like this.
Yao: Don't worry, Pang, they're just some bandits. No match for me.
Pang: But...
Yao: Pang, I'm doing this for the Tiger Tribe. If you're my friend, then don't stop me.
Pang: You're too impetuous, Yao. You simply leave a note, then run off to Glassmaw Pond.
Yao: Hah! Because I knew a certain someone would come looking for me.
Pang: Hmph, there's no talking sense into you...
Yao: Now, it's time to catch these bandits red-handed. Friend, will you lend your strength?
Yao: Not very discreet...
Yao: Is this really where the Bloodfang's leader is hiding?
Yao: I guess Glassmaw Pond really hasn't changed... Pond scum isn't the only type of scum that dwells here...
Yao: Trying to follow me, hmm? You should have learned to keep your footsteps quieter.
Yao: It's you...
Joo-Won: My instincts were correct, it seems. I thought you'd come through this hidden path... Night Wanderer.
Joo-Won: I've heard many rumors about you... Bandits and traitors fear you.
Joo-Won: To be honest, I've admired you for a long time. I'm ashamed that I didn't realize it was you from the get-go.
Yao: And now you follow me... for what reason?
Joo-Won: It is also my aim to eradicate the Bloodfangs. I still think it would be most prudent for us to unite our efforts.
Yao: And I'm still saying no.
Joo-Won: Why, Night Wanderer? Because you work best alone?
Yao: ...Our goal may be the same, and yet we are not the same.
Joo-Won: Yes, I'm quite aware we do not see eye to eye on certain... moral issues.
Joo-Won: And yet I can sense we still pine for the same justice.
Yao: Justice... Hmph!
Joo-Won: Are you not fighting for justice? Then what are you fighting for?
Yao: I have no time for moral pontifications.
Joo-Won: Hey! Night Wanderer!?
Yao: There hasn't been a soul on this path so far... they must have been tipped off.
Joo-Won: Or... we've been lied to. Maybe the Bloodfangs were never here in the first place.
Yao: Did you not understand me back there?
Joo-Won: You never told me not to come along. Plus, if you truly wanted me gone, you could have easily deterred me.
Joo-Won: Now, back to the matter at hand... I supposed that man back there gave you false information, to keep his life.
Yao: No... look closer.
Yao: This shack may be old, but these ashes are fresh. Someone has been here recently.
Joo-Won: ...Then we may be able to find more clues around here.
Yao: "We"? Hmph...
Yao: Just be quiet and look around.
Joo-Won: ...Night Wanderer, why do you walk this path?
Yao: Don't ask stupid questions, just look for clues.
Joo-Won: I simply want to better understand my companion.
Yao: No need.
Joo-Won: Have you always been so closed off?
Joo-Won: Back when I was a child, my village was harrassed by outside powers. They controlled our people through fear, no one dared fight back.
Joo-Won: Until one day, a wandering tiger came to our village. He stood up for us and brought justice.
Joo-Won: That day, my village's people were given hope once again, and I found my purpose in life.
Yao: What happened to the tiger?
Yao: Follower, I asked you about what happened to that tiger? Where did he go?
Joo-Won: He said he intended on turning those criminals in to the Alliance, and he left with them in tow.
Yao: So is this tiger your idol, now? You want to be righteous, just like him?
Joo-Won: You could say that... And yet, I've thought about it more recently.
Yao: And?
Yao: I don't think you understand what you've gotten yourself into.
Joo-Won: What do you mean? We may differ on how to deal with criminals, and yet I believe we have common ground!
Yao: And yet I'm a criminal too. Where does your moral compass point on that one?
Joo-Won: ...Why do you walk this path, Night Wanderer?
Yao: That doesn't concern you.
Yao: One day, you'll realize your beliefs are hollow. Such a farce, you'll want to laugh but won't have the strength.
Yao: And then you'll realize, you're a criminal, too.
Joo-Won: Is that so...? Then I suppose you don't understand where my belief comes from.
Joo-Won: Still... if that day truly comes, where I fall from grace... I beg you stop me in my tracks.
Yao: Hmph...
Yao: It's dark...
Yao: It's a trap!
Yao: There must be somebody behind that wall! Break it down!
Scared Girl: Yagh!
Yao: Don't try and run!
